docs.abstract: Amazon missed an opportunity to generate good will and bridge the divide between red and blue America by picking a city in the heartland.
docs.snippet: Amazon missed an opportunity to generate good will and bridge the divide between red and blue America by picking a city in the heartland.
docs.lead_paragraph: So, the Amazon bragging rights go to New York City and the Washington, D.C., area. Why do I feel a little deflated?

headline.main: Why Amazon Chose the Wrong Locations for Its HQ2

docs.abstract: A job at Facebook is plum. But at a recent university hackathon, some young engineers showed a changing attitude toward working at the social network.
docs.snippet: A job at Facebook is plum. But at a recent university hackathon, some young engineers showed a changing attitude toward working at the social network.
docs.lead_paragraph: BERKELEY, Calif. — A job at Facebook sounds pretty plum. The interns make around $8,000 a month, and an entry-level software engineer makes about $140,000 a year. The food is free. There’s a walking trail with indigenous plants and a juice bar.

headline.main: ‘I Don’t Really Want to Work for Facebook.’ So Say Some Computer Science Students.
headline.print_headline: A Social Media Giant Is Knocked Back on Its Heels

docs.abstract: Uber retreated from many towns in Germany in 2015 after battling regulators. Now the ride-hailing company has re-entered the city of Düsseldorf.
docs.snippet: Uber retreated from many towns in Germany in 2015 after battling regulators. Now the ride-hailing company has re-entered the city of Düsseldorf.
docs.lead_paragraph: DÜSSELDORF, Germany — Guido Goebel stopped driving for Uber three years ago when the company abandoned his hometown, the German city of Düsseldorf, after a battle with regulators.

headline.main: Needing Growth, Uber Returns to Germany. This Time on Best Behavior.
headline.print_headline: Seeking Growth, a Conciliatory Uber Returns to Germany

docs.abstract: The hedge fund billionaire Daniel Loeb’s latest activist push has him facing off against descendants of John T. Dorrance, who own more than 40 percent of Campbell and control three board seats.
docs.snippet: The hedge fund billionaire Daniel Loeb’s latest activist push has him facing off against descendants of John T. Dorrance, who own more than 40 percent of Campbell and control three board seats.
docs.lead_paragraph: Daniel Loeb is happy to play the barbarian at the gate. He’s got the money, about $3.1 billion. He’s got the office, a sleek white space that is a quintessential hedge fund aerie, with art by Jean-Michel Basquiat, Jeff Koons and Andy Warhol. And in taking on the old-money family that owns more than 40 percent of Campbell Soup Company, he’s found the perfect foil for his new-money ambitions.

headline.main: Campbell Soup’s Fate Hangs on Duel Between Company Heirs and ‘Interloper’
headline.print_headline: Maneuvering For Control  Of Campbell Soup Board

docs.abstract: Jonah Peretti, the chief executive, says his company could eventually merge with other online publishers in order to negotiate better terms with tech platforms like Facebook.
docs.snippet: Jonah Peretti, the chief executive, says his company could eventually merge with other online publishers in order to negotiate better terms with tech platforms like Facebook.
docs.lead_paragraph: BuzzFeed has long positioned itself as the future of publishing — it practices the mysterious arts of digital media better than anyone. From the beginning, its ability to know, before anyone else, what sort of content would go viral delivered it a large audience and helped the company attract half a billion dollars in venture money and a steady stream of mostly positive media attention.

headline.main: Founder’s Big Idea to Revive BuzzFeed’s Fortunes? A Merger With Rivals

docs.abstract: As concerns about growth and privacy issues took a toll, technology and banking stocks led a slide in Europe, and futures indicated that markets in the United States could follow.
docs.snippet: As concerns about growth and privacy issues took a toll, technology and banking stocks led a slide in Europe, and futures indicated that markets in the United States could follow.
docs.lead_paragraph: Apple was worth more than $1 trillion at the start of November. Now, it’s valued at $880 billion.

headline.main: Amazon, Apple and Facebook Once Led the Market. Now They Are Driving It Down.
headline.print_headline: Tech Stocks Dive As Wall St. Loses Gains for Month

docs.abstract: Many colleges and universities are taking a leading role in revitalizing local communities, recognizing that development can make their institutions more attractive.
docs.snippet: Many colleges and universities are taking a leading role in revitalizing local communities, recognizing that development can make their institutions more attractive.
docs.lead_paragraph: For decades, the University of Maryland has had a tense relationship with the residents and elected officials of College Park, a small city near Washington that the university calls home.

headline.main: Universities Look to Strengthen the Places They Call Home
headline.print_headline: The Gown Is Dressing Up the Town

docs.abstract: The network reproached Ms. Pirro, a star host, for suggesting that a Muslim congresswoman’s religious beliefs were anti-American. Tucker Carlson, another Fox host, is also under fire.
docs.snippet: The network reproached Ms. Pirro, a star host, for suggesting that a Muslim congresswoman’s religious beliefs were anti-American. Tucker Carlson, another Fox host, is also under fire.
docs.lead_paragraph: In an unusual reproach, Fox News on Monday criticized one of its star personalities, Jeanine Pirro, after the host questioned if a Muslim lawmaker’s religious beliefs undermined her loyalty to the United States.

headline.main: Fox News, After Rebuking Jeanine Pirro, Faces Another Uproar Over Tucker Carlson
headline.print_headline: Fox News Rebukes Star Host For Jab at Muslim Lawmaker

docs.abstract: For the first time in 20 years, the former anchor did not host NBC’s broadcast of the Macy’s Thanksgiving Day Parade.
docs.snippet: For the first time in 20 years, the former anchor did not host NBC’s broadcast of the Macy’s Thanksgiving Day Parade.
docs.lead_paragraph: For nearly a century, Macy’s Thanksgiving Day Parade has been a turkey-day tradition. For 20 of those years, so was Matt Lauer, as a co-host of NBC’s broadcast of the event. His presence was part of the day whether you liked it or not, like political bickering and your uncle’s weird, gelatinous side dish.

headline.main: Parade Watchers Are Thankful for Matt Lauer’s Absence

docs.abstract: The carmaker had found that Mr. Ghosn underreported his compensation to the Japanese government for several years. Its partner, the French automaker Renault, has been more cautious.
docs.snippet: The carmaker had found that Mr. Ghosn underreported his compensation to the Japanese government for several years. Its partner, the French automaker Renault, has been more cautious.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Nissan’s board of directors voted unanimously to remove Carlos Ghosn as its chairman on Thursday, three days after he was arrested on allegations of underreporting his income to government regulators over a period of several years.

headline.main: Nissan’s Board Removes Carlos Ghosn as Chairman After His Arrest
headline.print_headline: Nissan’s Board Removes Ghosn as Chairman After His Arrest
